questionTemplates.text:
W: Jean is certainly easy-going and friendly.
M: But her father is exactly opposite.
{a}

M: How long can I play on the playground?
W: Well, it opens at 9:00 in the morning and closes at 5:00 in the afternoon.
{a}

W: Hello. Is that Jim?
M: This is his father. He doesn't come back yet.
{a}

F: They came here the day before yesterday, didn't they?
M: No, they got here four days ago, and left yesterday.
{a}

M: Good morning, madam. Come in. What can I do for you?
W: Well. I'm having difficulty in sleeping. I often wake up at three in the morning and I just can't get back to sleep.
{a}

W: Excuse me, do you have any batteries? I need some to my radio, because mine isn't working.
M: Sure. They are over there, next to the pens on the desk next to the bed.
{a}

W: I dialed your phone number many times yesterday, but I couldn't get through. What's the matter?
M: Oh, there was something wrong with my mobile. I will have to buy a new one.
{a}

W: There is lot of food need to be prepared. I'm afraid I can't work it myself.
M: Why not find a cook to help you?
{a}

M: Did you enjoy your trip to St. Lous?
W: Yes, it was fun. We took a boat trip on the Mississippi River and saw a football game.
{a}

W: How long have you been at this school?
M: I have been here for about 8 years. I came here when I was 20.
{a}

W: Have you had a busy day at the office?
M: Yes, sorry I'm late. I didn't get the bus because Peter offered me a lift. But the motorway was closed because of an accident. I'll be even later tomorrow with the train strike.
{a}

M: The guests are leaving for New York today on the ten o'clock flight. We need someone to get them to the airport on time.
W: Ordinarily, I'd be happy to, but my car is in the garage.
{a}

M: What can I do if I can't finish reading it in a week?
W: You may come and renew it.
{a}

M: Yes, madam. What seems to be the problem?
W: I'd like to report a robbery. It's my ear. It's been stolen.
{a}

W: What do you think of the movie?
M: It was worth neither the time nor the money.
{a}

M: It's a lovely shirt. I'll take it. How much is it?
F: It's fifteen point fifty dollars.
{a}

F: Do you have a cat or a dog, Mike?
M: I have a cat, but I don't have a dog.
{a}

W: I'm thinking of going to Austin for a visit. Do you think it's worth seeing?
M: Well, I wish I had been there.
{a}

W: Did you go to the concert yesterday?
M: I had to do extra work in my office.
{a}

M: I don't think we can find a better hotel around here at this time.
W: Let's walk a little further to see if there is another one. I just can't bear the traffic noise here.
{a}

W: Do you have a plan for your vacation?
M: Last year I went to China, and the year before last, I went to Australia. But this year I want to stay home and take a good rest.
{a}
